      • AdobeLibraryErrorSyncLibraryDeletedOnServer

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorSyncLibraryDeletedOnServer
        A library that was changed locally failed to be synced because the library was deleted on the server. The library has been assigned a new id and the sync will automatically be re-attempted. The given library has the new id, and the old library id is in the error details.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorSyncNotEnabled

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorSyncNotEnabled
        AdobeLibraryManager cannot sync because the sync has been disabled by the client. Call AdobeLibraryManager#syncEnabled in order to re-enable sync.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorSyncNotAvailableDueToNetwork

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorSyncNotAvailableDueToNetwork
        AdobeLibraryManager cannot sync because either the network is not reachable or sync is not allowed for the current network status.
        See Also:
        AdobeLibraryManager.syncAllowedByNetworkStatusMask

      • AdobeLibraryErrorSyncNotAvailableDueToUserSession

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorSyncNotAvailableDueToUserSession
        AdobeLibraryManager cannot sync because the manager is suspended due to an authentication failure. This is because either no valid user session has been passed during startup or the user session has expired after the manager has been started.

        Clients should call AdobeLibraryManager.unsuspendSyncDueToNewAuthenticationStatus() to unsuspend the manager after they are sure the storageSession passed to the manager has now a valid authentication token.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorSyncWriteFailure

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorSyncWriteFailure
        AdobeLibraryManager cannot write a downloaded file. There could be a disc space issue. Clients should clean up some files.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorSyncUnexpectedError

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorSyncUnexpectedError
        An unexpected error occurred during sync. See underlying error for details.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorInvalidLibraryComposite

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorInvalidLibraryComposite
        This error occurs when the library composite is either corrupt or invalid.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorNoRenditionCandidate

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorNoRenditionCandidate
        This error occurs when none of the representations of the element can be used to generate a rendition.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorCannotLeaveLibraryOwnedByUser

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorCannotLeaveLibraryOwnedByUser
        This error occurs if the client tries to leave a library that is owned by the current user. A user can only leave libraries that are shared with them by other users. Clients should call AdobeLibraryManager.deleteLibraryWithId(java.lang.String) instead.

      • AdobeLibraryErrorCannotDeleteLibrarySharedWithUser

        public static final AdobeLibraryErrorCode AdobeLibraryErrorCannotDeleteLibrarySharedWithUser
        This error occurs if the client tries to delete a library that is shared with the current user. A library that is shared with the user can only be left, not deleted. Clients should call AdobeLibraryManager.leaveSharedLibraryWithId(java.lang.String) instead.
